body:

- Added `barmode` attribute to Barchart
- Added `nbins` attribute to Histogram
- Added `symbol` attribute to ScatterPlot
- Updated all usages of charts with new format
- Renamed vis.py -> chartx.py
- Moved Table to table.py
- Updated attribute in TextComparison [reference_text -> reference_texts]

Refactored UpTrain repository to support Generative AI use cases:

With the new changes, UpTrain can be used to:

Validate model's response and safeguard your users against hallucinations, bias, incorrect output formats, etc.
Experiment across multiple model providers, prompt templates, and quantify model's performance for
Monitor your model's performance in production and protect yourself against unwanted drifts


We have updated the documentation and will be making further changes to it.

title: Add an operator for BLEU metric as well as example for machine translation task
body:
BLEU is a metric commonly used in machine translation tasks. It compares the generated output with one or more reference translations and measures the similarity between them. 

BLEU scores range from 0 to 1, with higher scores indicating better performance.

title: Allow users to toggle bucketing options for calculating data drift
body:
Users can decide between:
- Percentile based bucketing
- Equally spaced buckets
- Gaussian buckets
- Custom buckets

title: Dynamically join Buckets in data drift clustering
body: During data drift calculations, we assume a fixed number of buckets and split the data equally among them. This causes issues when the data can have very few unique values. Ex: if the variable is tagged as continuous and it only has values = 0 and 1 in reference dataset, we should ideally have 4 buckets - <0, 0, 1, >1. But the current logic will split the data in 20 buckets with many buckets = 0 and remaining as 1

title: Save new keys in extra args in attach GT also
body:
While attaching Ground Truth in framework.py, we just update the Ground Truth column and not log if any of the new value is calculated and added to extra args. 

Check following code in uptrain.core.classes.framework.py
    def attach_ground_truth(self, gt_data):

        df = pd.read_csv(self.path_all_data)
        gt_id_indices = get_df_indices_from_ids(df, gt_data["id"])
        df.loc[gt_id_indices, "gt"] = np.array(gt_data["gt"], dtype="object")
        df.to_csv(self.path_all_data, index=False)

title: Extra args not handled correctly when GT is attached
body: In framework.py, we store extra_args as self.extra_args in "check and add data" func which we later use in "attach GT" func. This will create issues when GT is delayed.
